 Bashir Jamoh  CIOTA is a professional body dedicated to broadening and improving the knowledge, skills and experience of its members in the practice of efficient transport management or an intermodal mode basis covering road, rail, air and pipeline/petroleum.It was founded in 1944, in Great Britain, and organised throughout the vast transport industry worldwide as an association of professional transport managers and administrators with more than 30,000 membership strength.
   
The Chartered Institute of Transport Administration (Nigeria chapter), was incorporated as an autonomous transport professional body on September 22, 1986, under the Land Perpetual Succession Act Cap 98.The institute has grown steadily in membership within Nigeria, to more than 2,000 members, and attracted transport professionals from all sectors of the industry. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .